Company Overview of Greene Lyon Group, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Greene Lyon Group, Inc. develops and licenses technologies focused primarily on recycling precious metals (PM) from scrap materials and industrial byproducts generated across multiple industries. Its portfolio includes PM1 and PM2 technologies for recycling precious metals from a range of base metal substrates; TF1, a non-chemical process that uses a specific dielectric fluid in a proprietary application to recover chips from populated circuit boards for secure data destruction, for reuse, or as a first step to refine the precious metals in the chips; and PbL2 technology for recovering lead and glass from cathode ray tubes found in old TVs and computer monitors. The company was incorporated ...
Greene Lyon Group, Inc. develops and licenses technologies focused primarily on recycling precious metals (PM) from scrap materials and industrial byproducts generated across multiple industries. Its portfolio includes PM1 and PM2 technologies for recycling precious metals from a range of base metal substrates; TF1, a non-chemical process that uses a specific dielectric fluid in a proprietary application to recover chips from populated circuit boards for secure data destruction, for reuse, or as a first step to refine the precious metals in the chips; and PbL2 technology for recovering lead and glass from cathode ray tubes found in old TVs and computer monitors. The company was incorporated in 2010 and is based in Beverly, Massachusetts with a laboratory in Quebec, Canada.
